thread.title: Fulham 0-3 Tottenham player ratings: Harry Kane scores emphatic hat-trick in FA Cup rout
thread.title_full: Fulham 0-3 Tottenham player ratings: Harry Kane scores emphatic hat-trick in FA Cup rout

author: John Cross
title: Fulham 0-3 Tottenham player ratings: Harry Kane scores emphatic hat-trick in FA Cup rout
text:
Good handling, defence left him exposed, couldn’t have stopped goals. 
Odoi 6 
Solid but Son kept him on his toes for testing afternoon. 
Kalas 6 
Looks a good player, solid centre half if not the biggest. 
Ream 5 
His misplaced pass played a part in Tottenham’s opening goal. 
Malone 7 
Excellent performance at left back, bar switching off on opening goal. Malone was one of Fulham's bright sparks from the day (Photo: Ian Walton) 
McDonald 6 
Struggled to keep up with Tottenham’s movement in midfield. 
Johansen 6 
Steady midfield performance but little opportunity to create. 
Cairney 6 
Clearly a nice player, but was caught in possession in midfield a few times. 
Ayité 5 
Subbed early after failing to create many problems for Tottenham. Aluko didn't have the influence he would have liked (Photo: Clive Rose) 
Aluko 5 
Good on the ball, skilful and tidy but gave Tottenham few problems. 
Kebano 5 
Plenty of movement and pace, but Fulham need to be more direct. 
Substitutes 
Sessegnon, for Ayité, 57 mins 
Cyriac, for Aluko, 66 mins 
Parker, for McDonald, 74 mins Tottenham 
Nearly gifted a goal to Cairney with dreadful pass. Just recovered. 
Trippier 8 
Excellent performance, played a part in goals and great delivery. Trippier proved a worthy competitor for the right-back spot (Photo: Clive Rose) 
Alderweireld 6 
Solid performance, comfortable game and snuffed out all danger. 
Vertonghen 6 
First start in a month and a very comfortable return to duty. 
Davies 6 
Solid defensively, regained some confidence but Spurs miss Rose. 
Winks 8 
Excellent on the ball, keeps the game ticking over, big prospect. Winks had yet another fine game in midfield (Photo: Clive Rose) 
Wanyama 7 
Scrapped and battled in midfield. He has been an excellent signing for Spurs. 
Eriksen 7 
Provided ammunition for Tottenham’s forward line and assists for both goals. 
Alli 7 
Lovely assist for Kane’s third goal. Had chances. So important for Spurs. 
Son 6 
His pace caused problems but needed to get on the ball more. Kane scored a superb hat-trick for Spurs (Photo: REUTERS) 
Kane 9 MOTM 
Hat-trick hero. That is now 20 goals in 22 London derbies. 
Substitutes 
Sissoko, for Kane, 75 mins 
Dembele, for Winks, 79 mins
